That's trivial. I never imagined it would be possible, and feel silly for not adding a test in the first place. Feel free to incorporate this into your PR if you need to resubmit for any reason; otherwise I can open a PR later.
```diff
diff --git a/hack/xref-helpmsgs-manpages b/hack/xref-helpmsgs-manpages
index 6a2d627bb..fcc88854c 100755
--- a/hack/xref-helpmsgs-manpages
+++ b/hack/xref-helpmsgs-manpages
@@ -242,6 +242,12 @@ sub podman_help {
             if ($line =~ /^\s{1,4}(\S+)\s/) {
                 my $subcommand = $1;
                 print "> podman @_ $subcommand\n"               if $debug;
+
+                if (exists $help{$subcommand}) {
+                    warn "$ME: 'podman @_ help' lists '$subcommand' twice\n";
+                    ++$Errs;
+                }
+
                 $help{$subcommand} = podman_help(@_, $subcommand)
                     unless $subcommand eq 'help';       # 'help' not in man
             }
```
